<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 3:51PM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHERN MCCURTAIN COUNTY
THROUGH 430 PM CDT...
At 351 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Broken Bow, or 31 miles north of Clarksville, moving
southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Idabel, Broken Bow, Wright City, Haworth, Garvin, Holly Creek,
Glover, Oak Hill, and Golden.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
